Teddy: I don't know
if I can hide this

517
00:26:09,137 --> 00:26:10,413
much longer, man.

518
00:26:13,241 --> 00:26:15,137
You and I keep
going over and over.

519
00:26:15,206 --> 00:26:17,344
What am I supposed to do?

520
00:26:17,413 --> 00:26:18,827
Teddy?

521
00:26:20,172 --> 00:26:21,448
Are you on the phone?

522
00:26:22,931 --> 00:26:24,344
Teddy:
Yeah.

523
00:26:24,413 --> 00:26:26,275
Do you need to use it?

524
00:26:26,344 --> 00:26:28,068
No, it can wait.

525
00:26:32,379 --> 00:26:36,620
[church bell ringing]

526
00:26:48,241 --> 00:26:51,068
[people chattering]

527
00:26:55,896 --> 00:26:58,068
Teddy, I need you
to talk to me.

528
00:26:59,862 --> 00:27:01,724
I need you to tell me
what you saw.

529
00:27:01,793 --> 00:27:03,413
Just, what
I already told you.

530
00:27:03,482 --> 00:27:04,827
Come on, Teddy.

531
00:27:04,896 --> 00:27:07,000
-Look, can't this wait?
-No.

532
00:27:07,068 --> 00:27:08,586
If you have something
to tell me,

533
00:27:08,655 --> 00:27:09,965
then no, it can't.

534
00:27:11,172 --> 00:27:13,000
Tell me about Jeb.

535
00:27:14,137 --> 00:27:16,413
Well, this is
destroying him,

536
00:27:16,482 --> 00:27:19,172
this, people thinking
he did it.

537
00:27:19,241 --> 00:27:21,034
Did he tell you that?

538
00:27:23,379 --> 00:27:25,551
It's okay, son.

539
00:27:25,620 --> 00:27:28,000
Look, you've known me
for a long time now.

540
00:27:28,068 --> 00:27:29,310
You know I wouldn't
be asking this

541
00:27:29,379 --> 00:27:30,689
if it wasn't important.

542
00:27:30,758 --> 00:27:33,000
Now, talk to me,
tell me about Jeb.

543
00:27:36,482 --> 00:27:38,620
He asked me
to lie for him.

544
00:27:40,896 --> 00:27:43,517
He asked me to tell you

545
00:27:43,586 --> 00:27:46,068
that he left
before Katie did.

546
00:27:50,586 --> 00:27:52,034
And I can't do that.

547
00:27:54,655 --> 00:27:56,275
I just can't do that.

548
00:27:57,586 --> 00:28:01,310
So, they left together,

549
00:28:01,379 --> 00:28:02,448
that was the last time
I saw them

550
00:28:02,517 --> 00:28:03,758
and that's it.

551
00:28:05,034 --> 00:28:07,413
All right,
Teddy, thanks.

552
00:28:08,517 --> 00:28:09,827
I sure appreciate that.

553
00:28:09,896 --> 00:28:12,413
[dramatic theme playing]

554
00:28:30,034 --> 00:28:31,827
[Teddy sobbing]

555
00:28:37,793 --> 00:28:39,241
Oh, Mom.

556
00:28:40,482 --> 00:28:41,724
I know.

557
00:28:44,896 --> 00:28:46,551
I wanna go to her house.

558
00:28:48,413 --> 00:28:49,862
To Grandma's?

559
00:28:49,931 --> 00:28:52,551
To the cottage,
just the two of us, okay?

560
00:28:52,620 --> 00:28:55,310
Oh, honey, I have
to talk to your father.

561
00:28:55,379 --> 00:28:57,655
No, just the two of us.

562
00:28:57,724 --> 00:29:00,827
I need it to be
just the two of us, okay?

563
00:29:02,689 --> 00:29:04,000
We can leave tonight.

564
00:29:04,068 --> 00:29:05,620
We'll come back tomorrow.

565
00:29:07,620 --> 00:29:09,137
Please, Mom.

566
00:29:20,551 --> 00:29:22,448
Ed:
We should all go.

567
00:29:22,517 --> 00:29:24,379
He wants it
just him and me.

568
00:29:24,448 --> 00:29:26,655
Come on, Ed, don't give me
a hard time with this.

569
00:29:26,724 --> 00:29:28,620
I just think
it's not necessarily

570
00:29:28,689 --> 00:29:31,103
the healthiest--
Don't you see what I mean?

571
00:29:31,172 --> 00:29:32,517
He's very fragile
right now.

572
00:29:32,586 --> 00:29:33,724
Katie's death
has really hit him.

573
00:29:33,793 --> 00:29:35,310
Well, it's hit
all of us hard.

574
00:29:35,379 --> 00:29:38,241
-Rini, he's almost 20
and he can't be--
-Ed, he and I talk.

575
00:29:38,310 --> 00:29:39,862
We can talk.

576
00:29:39,931 --> 00:29:43,310
We always have been able to,
about things.

577
00:29:43,379 --> 00:29:46,068
God, he and I have been
through so much together.

578
00:29:46,137 --> 00:29:47,655
Ed:
I know you have.

579
00:29:47,724 --> 00:29:49,931
Teddy:
Come on, Mom, let's go.

580
00:29:50,000 --> 00:29:51,724
All of it, really.

581
00:29:51,793 --> 00:29:53,689
He was my support.

582
00:29:55,275 --> 00:29:56,517
Ed:
I guess I'm jealous.

583
00:29:56,586 --> 00:29:58,448
I wish he and I had
that kind of relationship.

584
00:29:58,517 --> 00:30:01,137
-How could you?
-I know.

585
00:30:01,206 --> 00:30:03,172
I'd be up in our room
with the door closed,
feeling like--

586
00:30:03,241 --> 00:30:05,379
-The room was spinning.
-But not so drunk I didn't know

587
00:30:05,448 --> 00:30:07,172
my family was downstairs
living a life without me

588
00:30:07,241 --> 00:30:08,758
and a lot of the times
he had to...

589
00:30:08,827 --> 00:30:10,551
pull my weight around here.

590
00:30:14,448 --> 00:30:17,896
God, Rini, you know,
when I started drinking,

591
00:30:17,965 --> 00:30:19,931
you know what it did
to me when Joey died.

592
00:30:21,551 --> 00:30:23,551
-I was there.
-[slams drawer closed]

593
00:30:23,620 --> 00:30:24,931
And you handled it
in your own way.

594
00:30:28,241 --> 00:30:29,965
At least I slept at home
in my own bed every night

595
00:30:30,034 --> 00:30:31,172
and not in someone else's.

596
00:30:31,241 --> 00:30:32,379
[zipper rasps]

597
00:30:32,448 --> 00:30:33,655
I'm not playing
this game with you, Ed,

598
00:30:33,724 --> 00:30:35,517
I'm not doing it.

599
00:30:35,586 --> 00:30:36,758
Ed: I know.

600
00:30:36,827 --> 00:30:38,241
You can't.

601
00:30:45,827 --> 00:30:47,275
We'll be back
tomorrow, late.

602
00:30:48,379 --> 00:30:50,620
Ed: Are you gonna tell him
about the cottage?

603
00:30:50,689 --> 00:30:52,413
I suppose I'll have to.

604
00:30:58,482 --> 00:30:59,551
Drive safe.

605
00:31:03,896 --> 00:31:06,000
[dramatic theme playing]

606
00:31:12,275 --> 00:31:13,896
[horse whinnies]

607
00:31:47,275 --> 00:31:51,241
Oh, this place screams
for a good cleaning.

608
00:32:00,379 --> 00:32:03,103
Grandma used to read
to us in this chair.

609
00:32:09,206 --> 00:32:10,551
God, I wish
she was still here.

610
00:32:11,586 --> 00:32:13,068
Irene:
Oh, sweetie,

611
00:32:13,137 --> 00:32:14,620
I think
she was ready to go.

612
00:32:14,689 --> 00:32:16,551
Yeah, well,
I wasn't ready.

613
00:32:16,620 --> 00:32:19,344
[refrigerator door closes;
objects clattering]

614
00:32:19,413 --> 00:32:21,448
Sometimes it's like...

615
00:32:23,241 --> 00:32:26,965
She was the only one
who really saw me, you know.

616
00:32:27,034 --> 00:32:30,482
I don't know,
she just, she knew me.

617
00:32:30,551 --> 00:32:32,068
She knew
how I felt inside.

618
00:32:32,137 --> 00:32:34,724
Sometimes it was like
she knew my thoughts.

619
00:32:34,793 --> 00:32:37,413
Irene: Yes, well,
she was one of a kind.

620
00:32:40,448 --> 00:32:42,413
Yeah, she was.

621
00:32:45,517 --> 00:32:47,000
She really was.

622
00:32:52,034 --> 00:32:54,310
I feel so alone now
without her.

623
00:32:56,517 --> 00:33:00,068
I don't know if I'll ever
have that again with anyone.

624
00:33:02,896 --> 00:33:04,896
Don't you miss her?

625
00:33:04,965 --> 00:33:06,896
Of course I do,
she was my mother.

626
00:33:08,068 --> 00:33:09,310
What a question.

627
00:33:16,068 --> 00:33:17,103
I'll make a fire.

628
00:33:25,586 --> 00:33:28,103
Maybe I'll stay here
for a while.

629
00:33:28,172 --> 00:33:31,172
I mean, you guys hardly
ever use the place.

630
00:33:31,241 --> 00:33:33,758
Oh, honey, I--
I don't know.

631
00:33:33,827 --> 00:33:35,241
What?

632
00:33:35,310 --> 00:33:37,793
I mean, I can get
a job around here.

633
00:33:37,862 --> 00:33:40,586
Your dad and I, we're--
This place needs so much work

634
00:33:40,655 --> 00:33:42,758
and we just don't
have the money.

635
00:33:42,827 --> 00:33:44,482
You don't need money.

636
00:33:44,551 --> 00:33:46,827
I'll do the work.

637
00:33:46,896 --> 00:33:48,344
It's not a question
of that.

638
00:33:51,103 --> 00:33:53,517
Our finances are not
the greatest right now

639
00:33:53,586 --> 00:33:56,379
and I'm afraid we're
going to have to sell it.

640
00:33:58,241 --> 00:33:59,827
We just don't have
a choice.

641
00:34:02,931 --> 00:34:04,206
Yes, you do.

642
00:34:07,689 --> 00:34:10,034
-You just don't want it.
-Teddy--

643
00:34:10,103 --> 00:34:13,137
-You don't want it
to remind you.
-[objects clatter]

644
00:34:13,206 --> 00:34:15,758
You know,
you don't see, Mom,

645
00:34:15,827 --> 00:34:19,241
this is
my one place, you know.

646
00:34:19,310 --> 00:34:22,000
You never see me
in any of this.

647
00:34:24,862 --> 00:34:26,413
You could
never be like Grandma.

648
00:34:26,482 --> 00:34:27,896
[scoffs]

649
00:34:27,965 --> 00:34:29,827
You can say that again.

650
00:34:29,896 --> 00:34:32,172
In her eyes,
I was never enough.

651
00:34:32,241 --> 00:34:34,068
Grandma saw
the truth, Mom.

652
00:34:35,482 --> 00:34:37,413
You see
as you need it to be.

653
00:34:41,448 --> 00:34:42,551
That's not really fair.

654
00:34:42,620 --> 00:34:44,551
You-you-you have
this image in your head,

655
00:34:44,620 --> 00:34:46,620
like every time
you look at me,

656
00:34:46,689 --> 00:34:49,034
-I feel like you wanna see Joey.
-Teddy, please.

657
00:34:49,103 --> 00:34:51,448
-And I have a life, too, Mom.
-I know you do.

658
00:34:51,517 --> 00:34:54,344
-What about me?
I have a life, too!
-Of course you do.

659
00:34:54,413 --> 00:34:55,862
Well, don't you
and Dad ever get tired

660
00:34:55,931 --> 00:34:57,482
of screwing it up?!

661
00:35:01,000 --> 00:35:02,103
[door slams]

662
00:35:04,379 --> 00:35:05,482
[door slams]

663
00:35:08,620 --> 00:35:11,275
[people chattering]

664
00:35:11,344 --> 00:35:13,586
-Irene: Thank you.
-Both: Thanks! Heh.

665
00:35:13,655 --> 00:35:15,965
So, what do you think?

666
00:35:16,034 --> 00:35:17,827
I think their parents are going
to have heart attacks

667
00:35:17,896 --> 00:35:19,482
when their get
their credit card bills.

668
00:35:19,551 --> 00:35:22,586
I'm talking about Teddy
and Val going out.

669
00:35:23,793 --> 00:35:25,103
He never told me that.

670
00:35:25,172 --> 00:35:26,586
Oh. Well, I guess
some things

671
00:35:26,655 --> 00:35:28,241
a boy just doesn't know
how to tell his mother.

672
00:35:28,310 --> 00:35:30,896
[suspenseful theme playing]

673
00:35:36,000 --> 00:35:36,965
[computer beeps]

674
00:35:37,034 --> 00:35:38,551
[dog barking in distance]

675
00:35:42,793 --> 00:35:43,896
 [woman moans]

676
00:35:51,310 --> 00:35:52,724
[keyboard clacking]

677
00:36:04,137 --> 00:36:05,620
Woman 1: You inspire me.

678
00:36:05,689 --> 00:36:07,862
Man: Hey, did you see
that window over there?

679
00:36:18,275 --> 00:36:20,379
Woman 2:
Can they do that?

680
00:36:20,448 --> 00:36:22,758
Woman 3:
I can't believe this. Heh.

681
00:36:36,965 --> 00:36:39,137
Young man,
what in God's name--

682
00:36:39,206 --> 00:36:41,137
Yeah, huh,
this is gonna stop traffic.

683
00:36:41,206 --> 00:36:43,241
Teddy, Teddy, stop.

684
00:36:43,310 --> 00:36:45,344
-They're gonna mob this place.
-Right now.

685
00:36:45,413 --> 00:36:47,275
Teddy: No, no, it's like
that store in New York

686
00:36:47,344 --> 00:36:49,586
where they did all the windows,
it caused all that attention.

687
00:36:49,655 --> 00:36:51,655
This is not New York!

688
00:36:51,724 --> 00:36:53,068
Now, I told you to stop.

689
00:36:53,137 --> 00:36:56,241
Now, get this merchandise
out of it right now.

690
00:36:57,931 --> 00:36:59,620
It won prizes.

691
00:36:59,689 --> 00:37:01,206
Get out of this window!

692
00:37:02,793 --> 00:37:04,586
Get out of this store!

693
00:37:04,655 --> 00:37:06,206
Now!

694
00:37:06,275 --> 00:37:08,000
[beeping]

695
00:37:15,896 --> 00:37:17,103
 [girl moans]

696
00:37:17,172 --> 00:37:19,758
"Welcome back, Master"?

697
00:37:19,827 --> 00:37:21,965
"Tell me what you'd do to me."

698
00:37:26,206 --> 00:37:28,689
Hey, sport,
what are you working on?

699
00:37:31,655 --> 00:37:33,206
Go on, get outta here!

700
00:37:34,517 --> 00:37:35,827
-Jana: Dad?
-Where's Teddy?!

701
00:37:35,896 --> 00:37:38,448
Uh, he had a date I think.
Is Mom still at work?

702
00:37:38,517 --> 00:37:40,793
You and Scott go get ready
and we will go eat.

703
00:37:40,862 --> 00:37:41,862
Go on.

704
00:37:49,034 --> 00:37:50,137
[door closes]

705
00:37:52,379 --> 00:37:54,965
[electronic jazz music
playing over speakers]

706
00:37:58,068 --> 00:38:00,241
[people chattering]

707
00:38:08,862 --> 00:38:10,896
Katie: I would love to get
a hold of your hair.

708
00:38:10,965 --> 00:38:13,551
-[Teddy chuckles]
-Why don't you let me cut it?

709
00:38:13,620 --> 00:38:16,724
Because I don't really
know you that well.

710
00:38:16,793 --> 00:38:18,965
I bet you're good, though.

711
00:38:19,034 --> 00:38:20,551
I don't have
an artistic bone

712
00:38:20,620 --> 00:38:23,482
in my body, but yeah,
it's my art, they say.

713
00:38:25,689 --> 00:38:27,413
I do wanna open
my own shop one day.

714
00:38:28,758 --> 00:38:30,206
I hope you do.

715
00:38:33,724 --> 00:38:36,862
See, I think there's
an artistic soul in everyone.

716
00:38:36,931 --> 00:38:39,103
It's just waiting
to come out.

717
00:38:39,172 --> 00:38:42,344
Well, if that's the case,
then mine is buried pretty deep.

718
00:38:42,413 --> 00:38:46,413
Right. It just gets
all squelched in you.

719
00:38:46,482 --> 00:38:48,379
Maybe you had a teacher

720
00:38:48,448 --> 00:38:51,275
or your parents
got you all inhibited,

721
00:38:51,344 --> 00:38:53,172
and told you you
weren't good enough.

722
00:38:54,482 --> 00:38:55,724
Maybe you had
a brother or sister

723
00:38:55,793 --> 00:38:57,793
that was better
at it than you were

724
00:38:57,862 --> 00:39:01,931
and nobody ever noticed
what you could do.

725
00:39:16,965 --> 00:39:18,344
Irene:
Teddy.

726
00:39:18,413 --> 00:39:19,896
I worked at that
store for 10 years.

727
00:39:19,965 --> 00:39:21,965
How can I show
my face in there again?

728
00:39:23,310 --> 00:39:25,000
Don't. I'm not gonna.

729
00:39:25,068 --> 00:39:26,931
Come on, Mom,
you can find a place

730
00:39:27,000 --> 00:39:28,551
better than
that for your talents.

731
00:39:28,620 --> 00:39:29,931
It's not your place to decide
where your mother works.

732
00:39:30,000 --> 00:39:31,517
What you did
was inexcusable.

733
00:39:31,586 --> 00:39:33,896
Oh, you are blowing this
way out of proportion.

734
00:39:33,965 --> 00:39:35,344
Ed: I'm not blowing anything
out of proportion,

735
00:39:35,413 --> 00:39:36,896
including the fact that
you left your computer on

736
00:39:36,965 --> 00:39:38,517
for some disgusting
internet slut

737
00:39:38,586 --> 00:39:40,655
to send you pornography.

738
00:39:40,724 --> 00:39:42,482
You went in my room?

739
00:39:42,551 --> 00:39:44,241
Never mind that.

740
00:39:44,310 --> 00:39:46,068
No, I don't go
through your damn room!

741
00:39:46,137 --> 00:39:47,413
Well, it was
your little brother

742
00:39:47,482 --> 00:39:49,793
who was in there
reading that crap.

743
00:39:49,862 --> 00:39:51,586
A lot has changed
in the last year, son.

744
00:39:51,655 --> 00:39:54,413
I am sober and we are trying
to rebuild this family.

745
00:39:54,482 --> 00:39:57,206
Right, without me.

746
00:39:58,965 --> 00:40:01,034
-Don't say that.
-Oh, I can see.

747
00:40:01,103 --> 00:40:03,172
You've always wished
I would have been
the one who died.

748
00:40:03,241 --> 00:40:05,655
I wish I was the one who died!
Teddy, how can you even--

749
00:40:05,724 --> 00:40:07,551
-If Joey hadn't started that
fire, he would still be here...
-Ed: Stop it!

750
00:40:07,620 --> 00:40:09,448
...and he would still
be your favorite!

751
00:40:09,517 --> 00:40:11,413
Stop it.
I said stop it.

752
00:40:11,482 --> 00:40:13,862
I know how much
he meant to you.

753
00:40:13,931 --> 00:40:15,620
No, no, this is not about him.
This is about you.

754
00:40:15,689 --> 00:40:16,655
This is about
you taking responsibility

755
00:40:16,724 --> 00:40:18,103
for your own actions.

756
00:40:18,172 --> 00:40:20,379
Now, listen to me.

757
00:40:20,448 --> 00:40:22,172
Now, either you get on track

758
00:40:22,241 --> 00:40:23,655
and you get a job

759
00:40:23,724 --> 00:40:25,413
and you keep a job or--

760
00:40:25,482 --> 00:40:26,655
Or what?

761
00:40:28,482 --> 00:40:30,379
Or what, Dad,
what are you gonna throw me out?

762
00:40:30,448 --> 00:40:31,965
Yes.

763
00:40:32,034 --> 00:40:34,103
No, no one is
throwing anybody out.

764
00:40:34,172 --> 00:40:35,724
It doesn't have
to come to that.

765
00:40:35,793 --> 00:40:36,965
That's right,
Mother.

766
00:40:37,034 --> 00:40:38,655
We wouldn't want
to give anyone

767
00:40:38,724 --> 00:40:40,206
the wrong impression,
would we?

768
00:40:40,275 --> 00:40:42,172
-Ed: Teddy, enough.
