[music box plays two notes]

1277
01:12:13,724 --> 01:12:17,724
[music box playing
"Hush Little Baby,
Don't Say a Word"]

1278
01:12:21,379 --> 01:12:23,034
Scott: Mommy!

1279
01:12:23,103 --> 01:12:24,344
Mommy!

1280
01:12:24,413 --> 01:12:26,482
Scott?
Scott?

1281
01:12:27,620 --> 01:12:30,068
Honey, what is it?
What is it?

1282
01:12:31,551 --> 01:12:33,862
Tell me, what is it?
I'm right here.

1283
01:12:33,931 --> 01:12:35,551
I...

1284
01:12:35,620 --> 01:12:39,310
I had a bad dream that you
and Daddy sent me away.

1285
01:12:39,379 --> 01:12:43,413
Oh, honey, we would
never do that. We love you.

1286
01:12:43,482 --> 01:12:45,517
But what if
I was really bad?

1287
01:12:45,586 --> 01:12:47,862
You're not bad.
You're a good boy.

1288
01:12:49,344 --> 01:12:53,275
I know, but I could
grow up to be bad

1289
01:12:53,344 --> 01:12:55,172
and then you would always
be really mad at me

1290
01:12:55,241 --> 01:12:56,862
like with Teddy.

1291
01:12:58,275 --> 01:13:02,655
No, honey, no.
We love you.

1292
01:13:02,724 --> 01:13:04,275
We love you.

1293
01:13:05,551 --> 01:13:07,758
No matter what happens,

1294
01:13:07,827 --> 01:13:10,310
we love
all our children the same.

1295
01:13:12,482 --> 01:13:17,137
You're Scott
and I love you.

1296
01:13:17,206 --> 01:13:19,137
And there's nobody,

1297
01:13:19,206 --> 01:13:22,551
there's nobody like you
in the world.

1298
01:13:22,620 --> 01:13:25,413
[crying]

1299
01:13:25,482 --> 01:13:27,482
[gentle theme playing]

1300
01:13:43,689 --> 01:13:45,482
[dramatic theme playing]

1301
01:13:47,551 --> 01:13:48,655
[car horn blares]

1302
01:13:51,000 --> 01:13:54,344
[tires screeching with swerves]

1303
01:14:01,310 --> 01:14:02,827
I have to talk
to you, Ed.

1304
01:14:05,517 --> 01:14:07,103
I don't know
where to begin.

1305
01:14:10,862 --> 01:14:12,241
You just tell me.

1306
01:14:14,827 --> 01:14:16,275
I'm so scared.

1307
01:14:17,758 --> 01:14:20,103
But I have to say this.

1308
01:14:26,482 --> 01:14:28,413
What? You tell me.

1309
01:14:31,241 --> 01:14:33,586
You know
what's in my mind.

1310
01:14:36,448 --> 01:14:38,137
And I'm so ashamed.

1311
01:14:39,275 --> 01:14:41,448
[sobbing]
I've...

1312
01:14:41,517 --> 01:14:45,034
-Oh, it's terrible...
-Ed: You've done nothing
to be ashamed of.

1313
01:14:45,103 --> 01:14:46,689
No, you haven't.

1314
01:14:46,758 --> 01:14:48,793
This has got nothing
to do with you.

1315
01:14:48,862 --> 01:14:50,931
You're not
to blame for this.

1316
01:14:54,000 --> 01:14:55,275
What do we do?

1317
01:14:56,862 --> 01:14:58,275
[quietly]
I don't know.

1318
01:14:59,586 --> 01:15:01,068
We have to be sure.

1319
01:15:05,551 --> 01:15:07,620
I think we have
to look through his room.

1320
01:15:07,689 --> 01:15:09,517
I already did that.

1321
01:15:09,586 --> 01:15:11,034
Ed:
What were you looking for?

1322
01:15:12,310 --> 01:15:13,827
I don't know.

1323
01:15:15,275 --> 01:15:16,551
I really don't.

1324
01:15:18,931 --> 01:15:20,931
Mike says he takes things
from the bodies.

1325
01:15:22,896 --> 01:15:24,896
What things?

1326
01:15:24,965 --> 01:15:26,724
Earrings,
he takes earrings.

1327
01:15:36,724 --> 01:15:40,965
[music box playing
"Hush Little Baby,
Don't Say a Word"]

1328
01:15:41,034 --> 01:15:42,793
[sobbing]

1329
01:15:55,862 --> 01:15:57,310
[phone ringing]

1330
01:15:57,379 --> 01:15:59,103
You kids
have a good time.

1331
01:15:59,172 --> 01:16:01,034
[car engine starts]

1332
01:16:01,103 --> 01:16:02,379
Sheila:
Goodnight.

1333
01:16:06,862 --> 01:16:08,724
[line ringing]

1334
01:16:08,793 --> 01:16:10,068
Isn't somebody there?

1335
01:16:12,586 --> 01:16:14,379
God, if anything
happens to her...

1336
01:16:15,862 --> 01:16:18,241
We have to go
to the police, now.

1337
01:16:19,241 --> 01:16:20,206
So, where
are you taking me?

1338
01:16:20,275 --> 01:16:21,620
It's a surprise.

1339
01:16:21,689 --> 01:16:23,482
Okay, then
just give me a hint.

1340
01:16:23,551 --> 01:16:25,448
It's my favorite place
in the world.

1341
01:16:29,103 --> 01:16:30,551
[dramatic theme playing]

1342
01:16:30,620 --> 01:16:32,068
[phone ringing]

1343
01:16:37,172 --> 01:16:39,172
[police radio chatter]

1344
01:16:44,655 --> 01:16:46,586
They match.

1345
01:16:46,655 --> 01:16:48,379
And one is Katie Whitehead's,

1346
01:16:48,448 --> 01:16:50,103
the other is Deirdre Cobb's.

1347
01:16:53,620 --> 01:16:55,137
You got any idea
where he might be?

1348
01:16:58,413 --> 01:17:01,827
The place, the bar
out on the truck route.

1349
01:17:01,896 --> 01:17:03,344
Yeah, yeah,
he goes in there.

1350
01:17:04,896 --> 01:17:07,724
Go home.
He might show up there.

1351
01:17:14,310 --> 01:17:15,413
[door closes]

1352
01:17:18,896 --> 01:17:20,310
[crickets chirping]

1353
01:17:28,000 --> 01:17:29,620
So this is
your grandmother's place?

1354
01:17:29,689 --> 01:17:30,758
Mm-hmm.

1355
01:17:30,827 --> 01:17:32,206
It's really cool.

1356
01:17:36,206 --> 01:17:37,551
Knives and forks.

1357
01:17:42,655 --> 01:17:44,655
[metallic clattering]

1358
01:17:48,413 --> 01:17:50,413
I'm really glad you're here.

1359
01:18:01,379 --> 01:18:03,758
Dear God, please
let them find him.

1360
01:18:25,034 --> 01:18:27,551
-Ed, turn around.
-What?

1361
01:18:27,620 --> 01:18:29,482
Turn the car around,
he's at the cottage.

1362
01:18:30,551 --> 01:18:31,586
He's at the cottage.

1363
01:18:31,655 --> 01:18:32,793
Hmm?

1364
01:18:36,724 --> 01:18:38,068
[tires screeching]

1365
01:18:40,482 --> 01:18:44,482
Teddy: I sat right here
with Grandma so many nights,

1366
01:18:44,551 --> 01:18:47,517
just looking
at the constellations.

1367
01:18:49,482 --> 01:18:52,241
She'd tell us
all these great stories

1368
01:18:52,310 --> 01:18:53,689
and myths about them.

1369
01:18:56,517 --> 01:18:59,379
And I'd ask her, "Grandma,
how much do you love me?"

1370
01:19:02,344 --> 01:19:05,448
And she'd say, "As much
as all the stars in the sky."

1371
01:19:08,172 --> 01:19:12,241
Heh. And I tried
to count the stars

1372
01:19:12,310 --> 01:19:13,896
and she'd laugh.

1373
01:19:18,241 --> 01:19:19,586
I look up there
and it's too much

1374
01:19:19,655 --> 01:19:21,137
to imagine them all.

1375
01:19:23,000 --> 01:19:26,482
How that light
just goes on and on and on.

1376
01:19:28,793 --> 01:19:31,241
To oblivion.

1377
01:19:31,310 --> 01:19:33,379
No, to infinity.

1378
01:19:39,379 --> 01:19:41,689
Come here.

1379
01:19:41,758 --> 01:19:44,413
What? I am here.

1380
01:19:44,482 --> 01:19:46,344
No, I mean come here.

1381
01:20:27,758 --> 01:20:29,000
Did you do this?

1382
01:20:31,448 --> 01:20:32,724
Who's Joey?

1383
01:20:38,448 --> 01:20:39,724
Hey.

1384
01:20:43,862 --> 01:20:45,275
What's wrong with you?

1385
01:20:45,344 --> 01:20:48,000
Nothing.
Nothing wrong's with me.

1386
01:20:48,068 --> 01:20:48,931
So...

1387
01:20:49,000 --> 01:20:51,137
Nothing's wrong
with me, you bitch!

1388
01:20:52,241 --> 01:20:53,068
Excuse me?

1389
01:20:53,137 --> 01:20:54,103
No, I-I-I bring you up here

1390
01:20:54,172 --> 01:20:55,620
to talk to you.

1391
01:20:55,689 --> 01:20:56,689
Just to talk,
to share something

1392
01:20:56,758 --> 01:20:58,310
very, very beautiful
with you,

1393
01:20:58,379 --> 01:21:01,137
and all you wanna do is
roll around like animals.

1394
01:21:03,103 --> 01:21:04,275
Just take me home, Teddy.

1395
01:21:04,344 --> 01:21:06,448
-No, look at me.
-Let go of me.

1396
01:21:06,517 --> 01:21:08,758
I said look at me!
You never even look at me!

1397
01:21:08,827 --> 01:21:10,931
-Teddy, what are you doing?!
-You walked down the hall,
you never even see me!

1398
01:21:11,000 --> 01:21:12,000
[Valerie screams]

1399
01:21:12,793 --> 01:21:14,620
Don't touch me!

1400
01:21:14,689 --> 01:21:17,275
I see you.
Please, I see you.

1401
01:21:17,344 --> 01:21:20,241
I spent my whole life trying
to be noticed by you.

1402
01:21:21,482 --> 01:21:23,310
What are you doing, Teddy?

1403
01:21:23,379 --> 01:21:24,655
We both died in that fire.

1404
01:21:24,724 --> 01:21:25,862
Joey was the lucky one!

1405
01:21:25,931 --> 01:21:27,413
-[Valerie screams]
-Teddy: Ow!

1406
01:21:27,482 --> 01:21:28,620
[Teddy grunts]

1407
01:21:38,344 --> 01:21:40,517
-[Teddy yelling indistinctly]
-[Valerie screaming]

1408
01:21:42,724 --> 01:21:44,931
You don't even know me!

1409
01:21:45,000 --> 01:21:47,000
Valerie:
I won't say anything!

1410
01:21:47,068 --> 01:21:48,724
[dramatic theme playing]

1411
01:21:50,448 --> 01:21:52,620
[Valerie struggling
and screaming distance]

1412
01:21:59,655 --> 01:22:01,172
[gasping]

1413
01:22:03,172 --> 01:22:04,482
[fire exploding]

1414
01:22:11,068 --> 01:22:13,275
[Valerie screams]

1415
01:22:17,655 --> 01:22:19,068
[car horn blares]

1416
01:22:22,275 --> 01:22:24,379
Ed: Valerie!

1417
01:22:24,448 --> 01:22:26,034
Valerie!

1418
01:22:26,103 --> 01:22:29,413
[music box playing
"Hush Little Baby,
Don't Say a Word"]

1419
01:22:29,482 --> 01:22:30,793
Irene:
Valerie.

1420
01:22:37,689 --> 01:22:40,172
[dramatic theme playing]

1421
01:23:00,310 --> 01:23:01,827
-[Valerie screams]
-Irene: Oh, God!

1422
01:23:01,896 --> 01:23:03,137
Honey-- Honey--

1423
01:23:04,344 --> 01:23:05,758
Ed.

1424
01:23:05,827 --> 01:23:06,896
Ed: Valerie!

1425
01:23:06,965 --> 01:23:09,000
-Irene: Teddy!
-Ed: Valerie!

1426
01:23:09,068 --> 01:23:10,206
Please, honey,
come with us.

1427
01:23:11,517 --> 01:23:12,793
It's gonna be okay.

1428
01:23:12,862 --> 01:23:14,137
You always say that.

1429
01:23:14,206 --> 01:23:18,551
And it will be.
Sweetheart? Teddy?

1430
01:23:18,620 --> 01:23:19,793
Teddy, there are ways.

1431
01:23:24,275 --> 01:23:25,620
We love you.

1432
01:23:25,689 --> 01:23:27,689
Your father and I
love you.

1433
01:23:29,000 --> 01:23:30,103
Please.

1434
01:23:31,551 --> 01:23:33,275
[sobbing]
Give me another chance.

1435
01:23:35,862 --> 01:23:37,931
Let me try to be
a better mother to you.

1436
01:23:39,724 --> 01:23:41,034
I want to try.

1437
01:23:42,310 --> 01:23:43,482
Teddy.

1438
01:23:47,965 --> 01:23:49,000
Mom.

1439
01:23:49,068 --> 01:23:50,172
Uh-huh?

1440
01:23:51,517 --> 01:23:53,793
Joey didn't start the fire.

1441
01:23:53,862 --> 01:23:57,000
I did, and then I ran.

1442
01:23:58,586 --> 01:24:01,068
It wasn't your fault, Mom.

1443
01:24:01,137 --> 01:24:02,655
Nothing was your fault.

1444
01:24:07,137 --> 01:24:08,551
Teddy, no!

1445
01:24:09,862 --> 01:24:11,517
Teddy, no, no, no!

1446
01:24:16,275 --> 01:24:19,517
No!

1447
01:24:26,137 --> 01:24:28,000
Teddy!

1448
01:24:28,068 --> 01:24:29,620
[eerie theme playing]

1449
01:24:41,379 --> 01:24:43,103
[no audible dialogue]

1450
01:25:02,241 --> 01:25:03,551
[Irene sobbing]

1451
01:25:18,448 --> 01:25:20,896
No!

1452
01:25:42,724 --> 01:25:45,827
Irene:
This is a scary world

1453
01:25:45,896 --> 01:25:47,689
and I worry
about my children.

1454
01:25:49,206 --> 01:25:50,862
I always have.

1455
01:25:56,482 --> 01:25:58,724
It's about my life.

1456
01:25:58,793 --> 01:26:00,413
Trying to control,

1457
01:26:00,482 --> 01:26:01,931
trying to...

1458
01:26:05,344 --> 01:26:07,931
Sometimes,

1459
01:26:08,000 --> 01:26:11,000
the oddest times,

1460
01:26:11,068 --> 01:26:13,137
I'll think I see him,
like in a crowd,

1461
01:26:13,206 --> 01:26:16,965
and this awful, awful dread
fills my throat

1462
01:26:17,034 --> 01:26:18,413
and I feel so guilty.

1463
01:26:19,655 --> 01:26:22,137
But then I think about
how much I loved him.

1464
01:26:23,620 --> 01:26:25,724
How much I still love him.

1465
01:26:25,793 --> 01:26:27,758
These things happen.

1466
01:26:27,827 --> 01:26:30,551
We're never gonna really know
why he turned out like that.

1467
01:26:30,620 --> 01:26:32,068
This wasn't you,
this wasn't us.

1468
01:26:32,137 --> 01:26:33,517
I know, I do know.

1469
01:26:33,586 --> 01:26:34,689
Honey, you tried.

1470
01:26:34,758 --> 01:26:37,379
We know how hard
you tried, we all did.

1471
01:26:37,448 --> 01:26:39,275
This is not
what we need anymore.

1472
01:26:40,724 --> 01:26:42,034
Let's get on
with our lives.

1473
01:26:43,275 --> 01:26:45,103
I can't.

1474
01:26:45,172 --> 01:26:47,517
I don't think
I can say goodbye to him.

1475
01:26:47,586 --> 01:26:51,068
We have to, it's time.

1476
01:26:52,758 --> 01:26:54,068
Sweetheart...

1477
01:26:59,068 --> 01:27:00,482
Okay.

1478
01:27:00,551 --> 01:27:03,793
Just give me a minute.

1479
01:27:03,862 --> 01:27:05,379
[dramatic theme playing]

1480
01:27:21,965 --> 01:27:23,241
Oh, Teddy.

1481
01:27:25,758 --> 01:27:27,517
My Teddy bear.

1482
01:27:30,655 --> 01:27:32,413
I tried my best.

1483
01:27:35,206 --> 01:27:36,793
I love you.

1484
01:27:39,862 --> 01:27:43,344
You're always
gonna be with me

1485
01:27:43,413 --> 01:27:45,068
wherever I go.

1486
01:27:48,034 --> 01:27:50,275
Wherever I go.

1487
01:28:15,068 --> 01:28:19,724
[music box playing light melody]

1488
01:29:11,896 --> 01:29:13,413
[laughs]

